<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <!-- Required meta tags -->
  <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"/>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=0">

  <!-- installed CSS -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/leaflet/leaflet.css"/>

  <!-- locally created css -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../stylesheets/style.css">

  <script src="/jquery/jquery.min.js"></script>

  <title>Final Project</title>
</head>

<body onload = "getAndShowData()">

  <%- include('partial/navbar', {active: "Home"}); %>

  <main role="main">
    <div class="row" style="padding:10px">
      <div class="container-fluid">
        <h1>Final Project  - TITEL FESTLEGEN! - auch in titel-Tab</h1>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" style="padding:10px">
      <div class="col-sm-12">
        <div>This application shows user and animal routes and their encounters all over the world.<br>
          DATABASE ERWÄHNEN?<br>
          For creating and inserting routes, use the menu item 'Maintenance'. There you can create your own routes by drawing them into a map or inserting a GeoJSON.
          Furthermore there is an option to search real animal routes from Movebank API which you can insert, too.<br>
          The tables underneath the map provide some information about the inserted routes and their encounters plus options to update or delete the created routes.</div>
          <br>
          <div id="indexMap"></div>
          <div>This map shows all marked routes which you can also see in the tables underneath.
            User routes are coloured red, animal routes are coloured orange.
            Confirmed encounters are shown in green, not confirmed ones in blue.
            If 'show only confirmed' in the encounters table is selected, you will see only confirmed encounters - but still all routes - in the map.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row" style="padding:10px; margin-bottom:40px; margin-top:40px;">

        <div class="col-sm-7">
          <h3>User Routes</h3>
          <div id="userRoutesTableDiv">
            <table class="table">
              <thead class="thead-dark" id="userRoutesTableHead">
                <tr>
                  <th>Consecutive number of route</th>
                  <th>Username</th>
                  <th>Name of route</th>
                  <th>Date</th>
                  <th>Time</th>
                  <th>Type of route</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody id="routesTable">
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <div>This table shows routes created by users as just planned or already completed.<br>
            The checkbox gives you the option to show or hide the corresponding route in the map above.<br>
            With the slider on the right the routes can be filtered by their name and/or their username.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <h3 style="text-align: left; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">Filter User Routes</h3>
            Username:    <input type="text" id="searchRouteUser" placeholder="Search users of routes" title="Type in a username">
            <br>
            Name of route:    <input type="text" id="searchRouteName" placeholder="Search names of routes" title="Type in a name">
            <div>
              <label class="switch">
                <input type="checkbox" onchange="searchEncounters('user', this)">
                <span class="slider round"></span>
              </label>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <div class="row" style="padding:10px; margin-bottom:40px; margin-top:40px;">

          <div class="col-sm-7">
            <h3>Animal Routes</h3>
            <div id="animalRoutesTableDiv">
              <table class="table">
                <thead class="thead-dark" id="animalRoutesTableHead">
                  <tr>
                    <th>Consecutive number of route</th>
                    <th>Study ID</th>
                    <th>Individual Taxon Canonical Name</th>
                    <th>Date</th>
                    <th>Time</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody id="animalRoutesTable">
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            <div>This table shows routes based on animal tracking data gotten from Movebank API.<br>
              The checkbox gives you the option to show or hide the corresponding route in the map above.<br>
              With the slider on the right the routes can be filtered by their corresponding study ID and/or the individual taxon canonical name of the animal.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-sm-5">
              <h3 style="text-align: left; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">Filter Animal Routes</h3>
              StudyID:    <input type="text" id="searchStudyID" placeholder="Search studyID" title="Type in a studyID">
              <br>
              Individual Taxon Canonical Name:    <input type="text" id="searchAnimalName" placeholder="Search " title="Type in a user">
              <div>
                <label class="switch">
                  <input type="checkbox" onchange="searchEncounters('animal', this)">
                  <span class="slider round"></span>
                </label>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>

          <div class="row" style="padding:10px; margin-bottom:40px; margin-top:40px;">
            <div class="col-sm">
              <h3>Encounters</h3>
              <div id="encounterTableDiv">
                <table class="table">
                  <thead class="thead-dark" id="encounterTableHead">
                    <tr>
                      <th rowspan="2">Consecutive number of encounter</th>
                      <th rowspan="2">Number of first route</th>
                      <th rowspan="2">Number of second route</th>
                      <th colspan="2" align="center">Context information</th>
                      <th colspan="1" align="center">
                        <div style="white-space:nowrap">
                          <input type='checkbox' id='showConfirmedCheckbox' name="showConfirmedCheckbox" onclick="onlyShowConfirmed()">
                          <label for="showConfirmedCheckbox">only show confirmed</label>
                        </div>
                      </th>
                      <th rowspan="2">Share Encounter</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <th>Country</th>
                      <th>Terrain</th>
                      <th>Confirm encounter</th>
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody id="encountersTable">
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
              <div>This table shows all encounters between any of the routes above. NUMMERNZUGEHÖTIGKEIT ERKLÄREN ?<br>
                Because the users do not specify timestamps for each point of their routes, the calculated encounters initially are just potential ones.
                By marking an encounter as 'confirmed' a user can save the encounter as having actually taken place.<br>
                To have some additional information, for example if you want to visit a place of these again, the terrain of the encounters' location and its country is shown.<br>
                To share a specific encounter with other people, you can use the URL given by its 'share'-button.</div>
              </div>
            </div>

          </main>

          <%- include('partial/footer'); %>

        </body>
        </html>

        <script src="/popper/umd/popper.min.js"></script>
        <script src="/bootstrap/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
        <script src="/leaflet/leaflet.js"></script>
        <script src="/turf/turf.min.js"></script>
        <script src="/jsnlog/jsnlog.min.js"></script>

        <script src="/javascript/apiRequestsEncounters.js"></script>
        <script src="/javascript/createAndFillTables.js"></script>
        <script src="/javascript/coordinateSwapping.js"></script>
        <script src="/javascript/encounters.js"></script>
        <script src="/javascript/index.js"></script>
        <script src="/javascript/tokens.js"></script>
